(487, 'AA487', 'Clinical, public health, and reference laboratories participating in the Stepwise Laboratory (Quality) Improvement Process Towards Accreditation (SLIPTA) are reviewed bi-annually. Recognition is given for the upcoming calendar year based on progress towards meeting requirements set by international standards and on laboratory performance during the 12 months preceding the SLIPTA audit, relying on complete and accurate data, usually from the past 1-13 months to 1 month prior to evaluation.', 'Clinical, public health, and reference laboratories participating in the Stepwise Laboratory (Quality) Improvement Process Towards Accreditation (SLIPTA) are reviewed bi-annually. Recognition is given for the upcoming calendar year based on progress towards meeting requirements set by international standards and on laboratory performance during the 12 months preceding the SLIPTA audit, relying on complete and accurate data, usually from the past 1-13 months to 1 month prior to evaluation.', '', '', ''),
